POTENTIALLY QUESTIONABLE MARKED ANSWERS:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q124: NOTE: Marked A='usage-based billing'. Q50(Part1) says B='subscription-based'. NC2 uses subscription licensing with consumption tracking. Both are partially correct - subscription is the model, consumption tracking is the billing mechanism.
Q163: NOTE: Marked B says 'AWS VPC with delegated subnets'. On AWS, subnets are not 'delegated' in the Azure sense. The term is more appropriate for Azure. But the intent is clear - VPC+subnets.
Q178: DEBATABLE: Marked C says 'all VM networking disrupted'. Per Nutanix docs, only north-south traffic is affected; east-west overlay traffic between VMs continues. B could be more accurate, but C is the exam answer.

================================================================================
KEY NC2 FACTS VERIFIED ACROSS ALL 320 QUESTIONS:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* AWS instance type: i3.metal (i3en.metal for max storage)
* Azure infrastructure: BareMetal Infrastructure
* AWS subnet minimum: /25 (128 IPs - 5 reserved = 123 usable)
* Azure delegated subnet minimum: /24
* AZ requirement: All nodes MUST be in same Availability Zone
* Foundation: NOT needed for NC2 (automated cloud provisioning)
* Flow Gateway: Azure-only (bridges AHV overlay to Azure VNet underlay)
* ECMP max: 4 Flow Gateway VMs
* Node hibernation: Both AWS and Azure (cost savings for dev/test)
* Licensing: Subscription-based with consumption tracking
* Metadata backup: S3 (AWS) / Azure Blob Storage (Azure)
* Minimum nodes: 3 (for quorum and RF2)
* Storage: Local NVMe only (no EBS/Managed Disks)
* DR: Leap for cross-cloud replication (on-prem <-> NC2)
* Migration: Nutanix Move (VMware/Hyper-V/AHV -> NC2)
* Management: Prism Central (unified across all environments)
* Key ports: 9440 (Prism), 2049 (NFS), 3260 (iSCSI)
* Routing: BGP (Direct Connect VIF, Azure Route Server)
* Encryption: Nutanix software encryption + KMIP for external KMS
